# Epic 4: Advanced Iframe Interaction & User Personalization

## Problem Analysis

- **Goal**: Implement a highly interactive and customizable user dashboard experience, including user-selectable menu positions, advanced iframe state management, clear visual indicators in menus, and specific interaction behaviors.
- **Key Requirements**:
  - Implement persistent user settings for layout and theme
  - Create robust iframe state management system
  - Build desktop "Top Menu" navigation experience
  - Implement desktop "Side Menu" navigation experience
  - Add click and long-press interactions for URLs
  - Ensure mobile compatibility for all features

## Current Status

### 2025-05-28 10:04

**Status**: In Progress

- What's working: User settings persistence, iframe state management, desktop "Top Menu" navigation with hover-to-expand functionality, desktop "Side Menu" navigation with collapsible panel implemented, and click/long-press URL interactions with visual feedback
- What's not: Missing mobile-specific adaptations for advanced features
- Blocking issues: None
- Next actions: Implement Story 4.6 for mobile-specific advanced features
- Documentation updates needed:
  - [x] User settings documentation
  - [x] Iframe state management documentation
  - [x] Navigation and interaction documentation

## Implementation Steps

- [x] **Story 4.1: Implement Persistent User Settings for Layout**
  - [x] Define UserSetting Prisma model with theme (Enum: `LIGHT`, `DARK`, `SYSTEM` default) and menuPosition (Enum: `TOP` default, `SIDE`)
  - [x] Update User model with one-to-one relation to UserSetting
  - [x] Create migration and apply to database
  - [x] Add logic to auto-create UserSetting records with defaults (`theme: SYSTEM`, `menuPosition: TOP`) whenever a new User is created
  - [x] Implement backend API endpoints:
    - [x] `GET /api/user/settings` to fetch the authenticated user's settings
    - [x] `PUT /api/user/settings` to update theme and/or menuPosition with validation
  - [x] Enhance NextAuth.js session data to include persisted theme and menuPosition preferences
  - [x] Create UI controls in User Settings page:
    - [x] "Layout & Appearance Preferences" section
    - [x] UI controls for menu position with static image previews
    - [x] UI controls for theme with themed preview boxes (selected has blue highlight)
    - [x] "Save Preferences" button that updates settings via API
  - [x] Add dynamic header adaptation based on preferences:
    - [x] Desktop: Three-section structure for "Top Menu" vs. hidden for "Side Menu"
    - [x] Mobile: Consistent header regardless of preference
  - [x] Implement dynamic dashboard layout based on preferences:
    - [x] "Top Menu" preference shows URL/Group navigation in AppBar's central area
    - [x] "Side Menu" preference shows persistent side panel for navigation
  - [x] Create theme application and toggle functionality:
    - [x] Use MUI ThemeProvider with persisted theme
    - [x] Support SYSTEM theme with OS preference detection (prefers-color-scheme)
    - [x] Fall back to DARK if OS preference undetectable
  - Success criteria: Users can personalize layout and theme with persistence
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (User Schema), Epic 2 (User Profile)

- [x] **Story 4.2: Implement Core Iframe State Management**
  - [x] Create IframeProvider React Context:
    - [x] Store managedIframes Map<string, { originalSrc: string; currentSrc: string; isLoaded: boolean; }>
    - [x] Track activeUrlIdentifier
  - [x] Implement useIframeManager custom hook with optimized methods:
    - [x] getIframeData(id), isUrlLoaded(id)
    - [x] setActiveUrl(id, srcForDataSrc)
    - [x] markAsLoaded(id), markAsUnloaded(id)
    - [x] triggerReload(id)
    - [x] getAllManagedIframesForRender()
  - [x] Add iframe rendering logic:
    - [x] Iterate getAllManagedIframesForRender() to render iframes
    - [x] Set src and data-src attributes appropriately
  - [x] Implement CSS visibility control:
    - [x] Active iframe: visibility: visible
    - [x] Inactive iframes: visibility: hidden; position: absolute; left: -9999px;
  - [x] Add iframe sandbox attributes for security:
    - [x] sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-forms allow-downloads allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox"
  - [x] Create mechanisms for tracking loaded status:
    - [x] Monitor onload (calls markAsLoaded)
    - [x] Monitor onerror (status remains loaded: false)
    - [x] Display UI error for active iframe load failures
  - [x] Implement state preservation verification:
    - [x] Test loading URL A, scrolling, loading URL B, then showing A again to verify state preservation
  - [x] Add support for initial URL loading:
    - [x] Integrate with Story 3.9's initial auto-load functionality
  - [x] Optimize for performance using memoized React Context and React.memo for consumers
  - Success criteria: Robust iframe state management with visibility control
  - Dependencies: Story 3.9

- [x] **Story 4.3: Implement Desktop "Top Menu" Navigation Experience**
  - [x] Create conditional rendering for AppBar central area:
    - [x] Render in AppBar central area if menuPosition === TOP and viewport ≥768px
    - [x] Replace simpler Epic 3 top menu navigation
  - [x] Implement normal state display with opacity/underline indicators:
    - [x] Display current selected group name
    - [x] Show horizontal row of URL items for current group only
    - [x] Display favicons (or fallback) and effective titles
    - [x] Visual states: opacity 0.5 (unloaded), 1.0 (loaded), blue underline (active)
  - [x] Add hover-to-expand interaction:
    - [x] Hovering triggers expanded view below AppBar central area (using MUI Popper/div)
    - [x] Expanded view shows current group + URLs and other groups + URLs with visual states
    - [x] Mouse-out collapses view smoothly with suitable delay
  - [x] Create expanded view interaction handling:
    - [x] Clicking URL calls setActiveUrl(), updates selected group state, collapses expansion
  - [x] Implement responsive adaptation for tablets (768px - 1199px):
    - [x] Horizontal URL rows have condensed spacing
    - [x] Overflowing URL rows become horizontally scrollable (touch-swipe)
    - [x] Add "More" (•••) icon that opens MUI Menu with overflowed URL items
  - [x] Ensure proper layout and scrolling:
    - [x] Fit within AppBar/popper
    - [x] No main page scroll
    - [x] Application maintains 100% viewport height
  - [x] Optimize for smooth animations (300ms) and efficient rendering (memoization)
  - Success criteria: Rich, intuitive "Top Menu" experience with visual indicators
  - Dependencies: Stories 3.8, 4.1, 4.2

- [x] **Story 4.4: Implement Desktop "Side Menu" Navigation Experience**
  - [x] Create conditional rendering based on preferences:
